with my weak animation and a cleric who is 38-39 we can duo<br>
right past the tunnel from the hidden valley in DL, doing the tundra yetis, spider people, dravogs, and giants. if you stay up the hill most mobs will not come to you and the agro radius<br>
of the mobs is small,, but soloing just to be safe have gate memed or a potion until you figure it out because there is no place to run, the exp is really really good there for some reason at 41 I was getting two and a half bubs of yellow every<br>
two hours, almost 43 now never had more than 2 or 3 in a group with me and everything was DB when I got there.<br>
but thats a enchanter talking, I have never played a mage<br>
but i have heard they are real good for soloing and if your earth pet can root you should be just fine, decent loot too sometimes 3-4pp with some gems dropping and gear that can be bazaared for 50-100pp, in the last two hour session i was there I got two emeralds, the giant lords tunic a few lumberjack caps, and a leg-chopper, nothing really worth much but I can get 200pp in the bazaar adding it all up with some of the smaller stuff, be prepaired with your pet and make sure it doen't get lost when you go through the cave form the valley to the DL, usually there is a Yeti or two hogging the trail. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/untitled.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf of Many Faces</span><br>  Posts: 613<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/16/03 10:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happy hunting grounds</span><hr size=1> I was the one who mentioned the Man-o-Wars in EW.  They are good and you could likely handle them.  They are good xp, and they drop those tusks more often that the Othmirs are willing to trade for precious gems.  But I don't know if they would be yellow to you.  They were blue to me till...wait a sec, they are still blue to me.  I just don't learn as fast from them any more. <br>
<br>
The big problem with them is the walrus are the common spawn and the Man-o-Wars are more rare.  I have seen up to five up at once while seeing 20 or so walrus.  Till I was 45 or so, all of the walrus gave me good xp.  After then, only about half of them stayed blue till about 48.  Now only the Man-o-War's give me xp but not enough to stay there.<br>
<br>
The Giants in Firona Vie would be good.  Just make your camp on the hill behind them and you'll not get any wandering adds.  You won't be able to sell to the FV merchants, of course, but I duo'd there with a druid for a few seasons in my later 30's and you can get wonderful experience and decent loot.  The pilgrims don't wander out that far from the town,and we have no wandering guards, so you won't really have to worry about being KoS to them.<br>
<br>
The only difficulty is breaking the fort.  If you pull one, they are just close enough together where you are likely to get them all.  Unless you are fast and can root them apart from each other so your pet isn't getting beat on by all three of them, you might have some trouble.  But after the spawn is broken, it is good hunting, and by the time you finish with the third, the first should be about to repop.  Xp is wonderful too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sulissaurnvelve>Sulissa UrnVelve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/19/03 3:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happy hunting grounds</span><hr size=1> Dwarves in butcher Block, old school but sorta fun *nods* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dididaryth>Didi D Aryth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Worshipping Tallonar since 3160</span><br>  Posts: 1079<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 1:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happy hunting grounds</span><hr size=1> Ooooo .... dwarves are doable at 38?  Must check that out!!<br>
